                  </persName>
             Watchman depos'd, That at Hatton-Garden near Saffron-Hill, he heard the Noise of Stop Thief, and immediately saw the Prisoner upon full Speed, whom he took, the Prosecutor then being in pursuit, and very near him, that when he took the Prisoner he cried out, Stop Thief, as if he was in quest of one, but this Deponent saw no other Person but the Prosecutor, who charged him with the Prisoner.</p>
               <p>
            
